test_TSH_Test_Diagnosis module¶

test_TSH_Test_Diagnosis.test_TSH_diagnosis_hyper()¶

Unit test for a list of TSH values corresponding to hyperthyroidism

This function is a unit test that receives a string of TSH values and tests whether the TSH_diagnosis code correctly orders the test results from low to high and outputs the correct diagnosis.

Parameters:
  • line (str) – line containing TSH test results
  • diagnosis (str) – asserted patient diagnosis
  • TSH_sorted_numbers (list) – asserted sorted test results (low to high)
